// Reduced-iteration sibling of `gc_loop_carried_ref.phx`, exercising
// the same non-entry-block parameter rooting: a ref-typed value
// carried across the loop back-edge as a block parameter must be
// rooted on every iteration or the accumulated string is swept and
// the next concat reads freed memory.
//
// 2000 iterations of growing-string concat allocate ~2 MB cumulative
// (sum 1..2000 bytes), crossing the 1-MB auto-collect threshold so
// the GC still fires while `acc` is the only live root chain — but
// small enough that the wasm32-gc column finishes promptly under
// wasmtime's GC, where the full fixture's 50k concats take minutes
// (host-VM GC throughput). The full fixture keeps the wasm32-gc
// opt-out; this one runs all five matrix columns.
function main() {
  let mut acc: String = ""
  let mut i: Int = 0
  while (i < 2000) {
    acc = acc + "x"
    i = i + 1
  }
  print(acc.length())
}
